A group of French business investors are in the country to established a world class first BIPV (Building-integrated photovoltaic) aluminum factory in Lagos to help curb the high rate of fake aluminum products Investigation revealed that the aluminum factory, when established, will provide jobs for about 100 young Nigerians for a start that will be trained for six months on the latest technologies in aluminum designs by Chinese expatriates scheduled to arrive in the country soon State of the art machines have been ordered for installation while operations has been billed to commence in August Similar factories it was gathered, will be established in Abuja and Portharcourt with Lagos serving as its base as the investors have decided to make Lagos as the China of tomorrow for Africa The factory which will have a massive showrooms will attract distributors across the country while a professional team from China will hold fair exhibitions It was also learned that the investors have plans to establish Plafond second project (plywood) factory and water park in the country after the take off of the aluminum factory